description
the primary function of the rqs business platforms group is to imagine design and implement the key capability needed to enable abbvie to have an industry leading technology-enabled regulatory quality and safety business function critical to that mission is building a data science capability that allows rqs to quickly develop accurate insight from evolving complex data set we have an exciting opportunity available for a senior data scientist within information research ir to leverage and extend our data science capability in the pharmacovigilance and patient safety pps space the ideal candidate will have a strong background in computer science with both data architecture and manipulation visualization skill a well a statistical modeling skill the candidate will work with senior scientist physician and technology group to generate data-driven insight related to the safety of our product the candidate will work with large internal eg pv safety data and external eg fda rwe data data set and a suite of analytical programming tool to generate deep insight for the pps group
key responsibilities
design understand key analytical challenge in the area of pharmacovigilance and work with senior scientist physician to structure analytical approach to answer question of interest dynamically design algorithm to address scientific query
build through your own effort or by working with software engineer develop custom software solution process that contribute to and help foster the growing abbvie data integration environment leverage existing tool set r spotfire d3 jquery apex net jreview etc to develop data visualization and recommend new tool that would benefit abbvie
presentation bring together disparate data type in compelling visualization package that provide end user with the ability to see both 'the landscape' and detail leading to improved decision-making
database support have the necessary skill to design and develop etls and materialized view posse technical proficiency in relational database technology to create physical data model
transactional system support integrate and generate data report on existing custom and vendor system
collaboration candidate will link pps stakeholder with ir team to solve data problem in a simple and agile manner
adaptability given our diverse mission you should be able to move fluidly between different project responsibility
qualifications
ms in computer science or related field with 10 year of experience in data science doctorate preferred
proven ability to develop solution in scientific programming language eg java c unix shell script python r
ability to develop web service eg rest based apis using j2ee and or spring
working experience in cloud computing service implementation eg aws google cloud
expert-level oracle skill -- including sql pl sql oracle trigger and jdbc programming
experience in data modeling integration and rdbms oracle db sql server
familiarity with big data ecosystem hadoop hive pig and nosql mongodb a plus
experience with unix scripting
familiarity with tool and technique for data analysis harmonization and visualization eg pipeline pilot spotfire seurat
ability to effectively communicate both verbally and in writing to scientist and non-scientists
ability to manage a multiple project with multiple team and collaboration